We do not consider the full range of possible $L^{*}/L_{\odot}$ explored by \citet{pawe15}, but restrict ourselves to the two illustrative cases of a sun-like $L^{*}=L_{\odot}$ star and a $\beta$-Pic-like A5V star with $L^{*}=9L_{\odot}$.
